06/07/2007
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Interior ministers from across Southeast Europe gathered in Bucharest on Thursday (July 5th) to discuss common security concerns and strategies against organised crime and illegal trafficking.
The ministers are expected to adopt a joint declaration and a co-operation plan covering 2007-2008.
(Nine O'clock - 06/07/07;
Fena, Focus, RTS, Radio Television Montenegro, MINA - 05/07/07)
